        <h3 class="blogh3">Senior Citizens Savings Scheme (SCSS): A Safe Haven for Retirement Income</h3>
        <p>Looking for a safe and steady income after retirement? The Senior Citizens Savings Scheme (SCSS) is a government-backed savings plan designed especially for senior citizens. It offers higher interest, assured returns, and tax benefits—making it one of the most trusted options for retirees.</p>
         
        <h3 class="blogh3">What is SCSS?</h3>
      <p>
        SCSS is a deposit scheme run by the Government of India for individuals aged 60 and above. It provides a regular quarterly interest payout and secure returns. You can invest a lump sum, and the interest is directly credited to your bank account every 3 months.</p>
      <h3 class="blogh3">Key Features of SCSS: </h3>
      <p><b>Attractive Interest Rate (Currently 8.2%) :</b> One of the highest interest rates among fixed-income instruments. The rate is set by the government and reviewed quarterly.</p>
      <p><b>Maximum Investment :</b> Up to ₹30 lakh can be deposited in a single or joint account. Minimum amount is ₹1,000.</p>
      <p><b>Tenure:</b>5 years maturity, extendable by another 3 years once.</p>
      <p><b>Interest Payout:</b>Interest is paid every quarter directly into your savings account—ideal for regular income.</p>
      <p><b>Tax Benefits:</b>Investment up to ₹1.5 lakh is deductible under Section 80C. But interest earned above ₹50,000 in a year is taxable (TDS applies).</p>
         

